[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-05T21:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/govee-backlight-set-32.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">A few months back, I was looking for a way to update my living room without replacing my TV entirely \u2014\u00a0something I\u2019m hoping to do probably around Black Friday / Cyber Monday. What I found instead was Govee\u2019s TV backlight set, which uses a small, mountable camera to read the colors on your TV and extend the lights past the screen itself. It\u2019s an added bit of luxury ambience that I adore, and right now through Sept. 7, you can get a full <a href=\"https://howl.me/cm1yekH63lC\">Govee Dreamview TV backlight and light bar kit</a> from Best Buy for just $89.99 (was $139.99). That\u2019s less than I paid for my own setup, and I\u2019ve been very happy with it.</p>\n\n<p class=\"ha", "id": 1091213, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/good-deals/448449/enlighten-your-tv-setup-with-govees-backlight-kit-now-36-off", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Enlighten your TV setup with Govee\u2019s backlight kit, now 36% off", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-05T20:45:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Betelgeuse (Michael Keaton) stands close to the camera with Lydia (Winona Ryder) out of focus in the background behind him in Beetlejuice Beetlejuice\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/MCDBEBE_WB036.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">\u201cI swear, the afterlife is <em>so random</em>,\u201d Jenna Ortega\u2019s angsty teen character Astrid Deetz grouses, deep into the action of Tim Burton\u2019s <em>Beetlejuice Beetlejuice. </em>It\u2019s meant as a tossed-off line, one of those \u201cWell, <em>that</em> happened!\u201d / \u201cOoh, <em>that\u2019s</em> gotta hurt!\u201d straight-to-the-audience statements that stand in for actual jokes. Instead, it lands like she\u2019s saying the quiet part out loud, laying out a mission statement for the entire movie.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em", "id": 1091214, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/review/448506/beetlejuice-beetlejuice-tim-burton-sequel", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Did Beetlejuice 2\u2019s writers abandon ship halfway through?", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-05T20:25:20+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Electronic Arts\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/Untitled-design-2024-09-05T161135.008.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">As we head into the fall months, <em>The Sims 4</em> will be exploring the scary subject matter of life and death. Electronic Arts shared a <a href=\"https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/news/the-sims-4-season-of-to-be-continued\">news post</a> on Thursday that reveals up coming kits, events, and the next expansion for the life simulator game. <em>Life and Death</em> will be an expansion pack that centers around the mortality and afterlife of our beloved Sims, and we can expect the return of the Grim Reaper for such an occasion.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Two new kits are set to release on Sept. 19: the Arti", "id": 1091215, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/448612/the-sims-4-will-expand-on-life-and-death-with-a-grim-reaper-expansion-this-halloween", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Sims 4 will expand on life and death with a Grim Reaper expansion this Halloween", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-05T19:51:40+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/LBR_IA_4-1_gallery.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Two of the best Muppet movies that don\u2019t feature the Muppets, <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24079265/dark-crystal-labyrinth-bundle-rerelease-jim-henson-cgi\">The Labyrinth</a></em> and <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2019/8/30/20838343/dark-crystal-netflix-age-of-resistance-skeksis-creation-myths-gelfling-mystics-urru-aughra\">The Dark Crystal</a></em>, are getting new, limited edition 4K Blu-ray Steelbook releases courtesy of Shout! Factory. While they won\u2019t launch until Nov. 19, you can pre-order either film (or both) exclusively at Walmart for $28.96 each. Fans of these flicks likely already know this isn\u2019t their first 4K release. However, both of th", "id": 1090834, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pre-order/448455/the-labyrinth-dark-crystal-4k-blu-ray-limited-edition-steelbook-pre-order-walmart", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Labyrinth and The Dark Crystal limited edition 4K Blu-rays are coming this fall", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-05T19:27:54+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/13045195/alan_wake_steam.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,14.907407407407,80.677083333333,85.092592592593\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Ground control to Major Tom, Remedy Entertainment is removing David Bowie\u2019s \u201cSpace Oddity\u201d from <em>Alan Wake</em>\u2019s credits and replacing it with a brand new original tune. Remedy announced that the song will be removed in an update on Sept. 10, something required due to \u201cchanges in licensing.\u201d Bummer!</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The new song is called \u201cStrange Moons,\u201d from <em>Alan Wake</em> and <em>Control</em> composer Petri Alanko. Alanko <a href=\"https://x.com/Peppepappa/status/1831740963368108257\">said in a post</a> on X the song is \u201cwritten from a point of view of an astronaut wh", "id": 1090835, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/448536/alan-wake-space-oddity-bowie-pulled-new-song-petri-alanka", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Remedy replacing Bowie song from Alan Wake over &#8216;licensing&#8217;", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-05T17:53:28+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A photo featuring a Space Marine 2-themed PlayStation 5\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/w40k-ps5-console-32.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gaming/447285/warhammer-40k-space-marine-2-review\">Warhammer 40K: Space Marine 2</a></em> publisher Focus Entertainment is drumming up hype for the game\u2019s impending launch with a sweepstakes that allows entrants to win a meticulously-crafted, absolutely unhinged PlayStation 5. </p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">From a hardware perspective, this is still a standard, disc-based PS5, but it sports the azure colors of the Ultramarines, the chapter of the protagonist of <em>Space Marine 2</em>, Sergeant Titus. The border of the console features a gilded edge with Imperial sk", "id": 1090018, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/448402/warhammer-40k-custom-ps5-space-marine-2", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This custom Warhammer 40K PS5 is a monument to the hubris of the Imperium", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-05T17:36:46+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Two Concord heroes face off in an industrial site that is lit on fire\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Firewalk Studios/Sony Interactive Entertainment\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/ss_bcdafae877274b30c0ec8dcb86f253479805d38b.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23375562/fortnite-dead-game-skin-epic-games-meme\"><em>Fortnite</em> is a \u201cdead game,\u201d</a> <em>League of Legends </em>is a \u201cdead game,\u201d <em>Overwatch 2</em> is a \u201cdead game\u201d \u2014 at least, that\u2019s what people online sometimes say. Despite people playing the games and developers supporting them, <a href=\"https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/dead-game\">the long-running meme</a> is commonplace in gaming, used to mock (both a game <em>and</em> the people that call the game a dead game), ", "id": 1090019, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/playstation/448419/concord-gameplay-final-hours-close-servers-offline-time-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Playing Concord at the end of its world", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-05T17:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/gravityfalls.webp?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">It\u2019s been over eight years since<em> </em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2016/2/23/11099696/gravity-falls-finale-weirdmageddon-part-3-childhood\"><em>Gravity Falls</em></a> ended, but the fandom is experiencing a mini renaissance. It\u2019s all thanks to <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24211450/alex-hirsch-gravity-falls-bill-cipher-book\"><em>The Book of Bill</em></a>, <a href=\"https://books.disney.com/book/the-book-of-bill/\">a new companion text</a> (if a book with a page dedicated to silly straws, a straight excerpt of <em>The Great Gatsby</em>, and a two-page advertisement for demonic Precious Moments-inspired tchotchkes can be considered \u201ctext\u201d) penned by the show\u2019s c", "id": 1089532, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/tv/447857/the-gravity-falls-resurgence-reminds-me-how-great-the-show-is", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Gravity Falls resurgence reminds me how great the show is", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-05T16:34:49+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Treyarch/Activision\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/black-ops-6-beta-header-1.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The <em><strong><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/call-of-duty-black-ops-6/443261\">Black Ops 6</a> </strong></em><strong>beta </strong>runs over two weekends in August and Sept., including an open beta for all players.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Unlike previous Call of Duty games, the early access beta period is available to all platforms, and not just PlayStation owners. Then, for those without a beta code, the second weekend will see access fully available as part of an open period. We\u2019re in the second weekend now, which allows you to jump in on Sept. 6.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">This page explains <strong", "id": 1089533, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/black-ops-6-guides/445111/beta-times-dates-code-early-access", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "When is the Black Ops 6 open beta start time?", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-05T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/LOTR_S2_FG_00344914_Still2224_R1_3000.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">Trust is a big deal, especially in Middle-earth. That\u2019s the key takeaway directors Louise Hooper and Sanaa Hamri and writer Glenise Mullins are keen to impart with <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/lotr-rings-of-power\"><em>The Lord of the Rings: The Rings of Power</em></a>\u2019s latest episode. It\u2019s a simple yet effective throughline that yields the second season\u2019s most focused (and satisfying) entry yet. And yet episode 4\u2019s emphasis on trust also underscores where it\u2019s missing \u2014 not just between our heroes, but between the show and its audience.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">[<strong>Ed note:</strong> This article contains spoile", "id": 1089534, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/lotr-rings-of-power/447801/trop-episode-4-review-bombadil-tolkien-lore", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 258, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Rings of Power episode 4 finds some footing amid its trust issues", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-05T14:53:40+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/ss_4862112e5030f74a5818cd4c31347d699ac5adf3.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24085031/balatro-jokers-break-the-game\">Weird poker-meets-roguelite game <em>Balatro</em></a> is finally coming to mobile, developer LocalThunk announced Thursday. </p>